class="de1">&gt;You give a tenuous sigh, before looking her dead in her wide blue eyes.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;‚ÄùHonestly, I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôve ever been annoyed into accepting a job offer, but, what the heck, I‚Äôll give it a go.‚Äù</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;At that her eyes shot open even wider, to the point that you thought she might hurt herself, and she squealed in delight.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;‚ÄùOH Thankyouthankyouthankyouwon‚Äôt regret this!‚Äù </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She was a practically vibrating, she was shaking so fast. </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;‚ÄùWe have so much to talk about, benefits, and vacation, and ohhhh I‚Äôm so excited!‚Äù</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;For such a small shark she was incredibly strong, and she quite nearly drags you off your feet when she attempts to pull you out the store by your sleeve. </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;This was gonna be an... interesting experience. </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">[Chapter 2: ‚ÄúHow to overcome writer‚Äôs block.‚Äù]</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt; ‚ÄúNo, no, no. I don‚Äôt like Xavier‚Äôs dialogue here. He sounds like a sociopath.‚Äù Mara said.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;It had only been a few weeks since your encounter in the coffee shop, but you and Mara had already begun working on her book.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Untitled, it was some kind of action romance, with the lead being a human renegade named Xavier, who was on a quest to stop the evil Dr. Jericho from destroying the world with a wonky, sci-fi device.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Content that, on any other occasion, would bore you to tears, you now had to read and write almost constantly.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&